(Experiment overview:) Tj
T*
(This synthetic demo describes an in vitro macrophage inflammation assay.) Tj
T*
(Cells were stimulated with LPS for 24 hours, then treated with candidate drugs.) Tj
T*
(The table summarizes IL-6 secretion in ng/mL for each condition.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Groups:) Tj
T*
(Control: LPS stimulation without drug treatment.) Tj
T*
(Low-dose Drug A: LPS plus a low dose of Drug A.) Tj
T*
(High-dose Drug A: LPS plus a high dose of Drug A.) Tj
T*
(Drug B: LPS plus a standard dose of a positive-control drug.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Biological context:) Tj
T*
(IL-6 is a pro-inflammatory cytokine. Higher values usually indicate a stronger inflammatory response.) Tj
T*
(Drug A is a candidate immunomodulator. Early pilot observations suggest high-dose Drug A may trigger cellular stress.) Tj
T*
(Drug B is expected to suppress or maintain low IL-6 levels relative to strong inflammatory activation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How to interpret clicked chart elements:) Tj
T*
(A clicked High-dose Drug A box with a higher median and wider IQR suggests stronger and more variable IL-6 induction.) Tj
T*
(Clicked High-dose Drug A outliers may represent samples with unusually strong stress or inflammatory activation.) Tj
T*
(A clicked Drug B box near or below Control supports the expected positive-control behavior.) Tj
T*
(A clicked Control box provides the LPS-only baseline for comparing all treated groups.) Tj
T*
